these are
all my AP classes.

32:21.339 --> 32:23.141 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: Are these your
grades?

32:23.175 --> 32:27.846 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARBARA GROH: Yes. For getting
an A, you can
get $25 to $1,000, depending on
the school.

32:27.879 --> 32:34.820 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: More than 140
colleges and universities
already, from Florida state to
Oberlin, Penn

32:34.853 --> 32:40.392 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
State to Notre Dame, using their
own formulas
to offer money in the form of an
eventual

32:40.425 --> 32:46.598 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
merit scholarship for high
school achievements,
starting in ninth grade and
guaranteed, though

32:46.631 --> 32:50.669 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
only if the student applies and
is actually
admitted.

32:50.702 --> 32:56.675 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Raise.me, a private company
funded by venture
capital and several foundations,
charges the

32:56.708 --> 33:02.681 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
schools annual fees to
participate. The scholarship
money is provided by the schools
themselves.

33:02.714 --> 33:04.583 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Take an honors or an advanced
course.

33:04.616 --> 33:09.588 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARBARA GROH: Participating in
an extracurricular
activity, taking the PSATs,
SATs, and also

33:09.621 --> 33:13.491 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for getting good scores, you can
