38:55.733 --> 39:00.772 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: For the "PBS
NewsHour," economics
correspondent Paul Solman,
reporting from

39:00.805 --> 39:04.976 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Miami.

39:05.009 --> 39:14.586 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now to Venezuela.

39:14.619 --> 39:20.692 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The oil-rich South American
nation is in the
throes of a deep economic
crisis, as its version

39:20.725 --> 39:26.864 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of socialism faces the crash in
global oil
prices and political turmoil.

39:26.898 --> 39:28.800 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Jeffrey Brown has our look.

39:28.833 --> 39:35.006 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: A symbolic
burning of the Judas,
something of an Easter tradition
in some Catholic

39:35.039 --> 39:38.977 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
countries. Effigies of unpopular
figures are
set ablaze.

39:39.010 --> 39:44.148 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This year in Venezuela, those
figures were
politicians, including President
Nicolas Maduro

39:44.182 --> 39:49.787 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and a local mayor. But President
Obama wasn't
spared. The U.S. has long been a
favorite

39:49.821 --> 39:52.090 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
target of Venezuelan anger.

39:52.123 --> 39:57.262 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Venezuelans have much to
enrage them right
now. The global price of oil,
the country's

39:57.295 --> 40:03.034 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
